      <h2>Understanding the refinishing process</h2>
      <p>A common question from Austin parents and pet owners is: "Will the smell be dangerous?" It's a fair question. The chemicals used to etch the tub and the coatings used to resurface it do have a distinct odor during application.</p>
      <p>However, once the coating is dry, it is completely non-toxic and inert. The key to a safe project is what happens *during* those few hours of work.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
      <h2>Professional-grade ventilation</h2>
      <p>At Austin Tub Surgeon, we don't just crack a window. we use high-powered industrial exhaust fans and ducting to pull air directly from the bathroom and vent it outside. This creates negative pressure, preventing odors from drifting into the rest of your home.</p>
      <p>In most cases, the smell is gone within a few hours of us finishing the job. We recommend keeping pets and small children in a different part of the house (or out for a walk at Zilker Park!) while the fans are running.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
